
[1]betroth

   BETROTH', v.t. [be and troth, truth, faith. See Truth, and Troth.]

   1. To contract to any one, in order to a future marriage; to promise or
   pledge one to be the future spouse of another; to affiance; used of
   either sex. "The father betroths his daughter.'

   2. To contract with one for a future spouse; to espouse; as, a man
   betroths a lady.

   3. To nominate to a bishopric,in order to consecration.
